	From: Rich Zellich &lt;zellich@ALMSA-1.ARPA&gt;

	You can't drop non-domain addresses from HOSTS.TXT because of
	all the MilNet hosts, which are \not/ yet required to use
	domain addressing.

Wait, maybe there's some confusion here. I thought all of the Internet
(including the MILNET portion) was to adopt domain-style addresses
(i.e., you had to at least join the ARPA top-level domain, administered
by the NIC).  It was my understanding that the MILNET was holding off
on the switching to the newer domains (EDU, COM, etc.) and also holding
off on the usage of servers to implement the hostname &lt;-&gt; address
mapping.

	The host I'm sending this message from, for instance, will not
	accept a domain address and I must occasionally "grep"
	HOSTS.TXT to get the old-style address so I can edit a reply
	address.

Not to sound like Mark Crispin (hi mark!) but your mailer should be
fixed.

/jordan

